**Iteration 5 complete.** Here's what was accomplished:

**Deep Research: `commands/` to `skills/` migration** → `commands-to-skills-migration.md`

**Key finding:** Migration is lower priority than expected. The official docs confirm `commands/` supports **all the same frontmatter** as `skills/`. Every improvement (allowed-tools, disable-model-invocation, context: fork, model overrides) can be done in-place without renaming directories. The only skills/-exclusive features (monorepo auto-discovery, --add-dir live detection, plugin packaging) are irrelevant for personal global skills.

**Recommendation:** Stay on `commands/`, add frontmatter in-place. Track directory rename as a future contingency only.

